📝 DRY-RUN PLAN — yage would perform the following actions
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

▸ Pre-phase
    • ClusterSetID = test-clusterset

▸ Dependency install — host CLIs for the operator
    • system packages: git, curl, python3 (apt/dnf/yum/apk)
    • Docker: install if missing; upgrade unless --no-delete-kind or kind cluster exists
    • kubectl      v1.32.0    (install)
    • kind         v0.24.0    (install)
    • clusterctl   v1.8.5     (install)
    • cilium       v0.16.20   (install)
    • helm         latest     (install)
    • argocd       v2.13.2    (install)
    • kyverno      v1.13.2    (install)
    • cmctl        v2.1.1     (install)
    • tofu         1.8.5      (install)

▸ Identity bootstrap — Proxmox (OpenTofu)
    • interactive prompt (PROXMOX_ADMIN_USERNAME / PROXMOX_ADMIN_TOKEN unset)
    • tofu apply: create CAPI user 'capi@pve' + token prefix 'capi-token'
    • tofu apply: create CSI user 'csi@pve' + token prefix 'csi-token'
    • outputs piped into clusterctl + CSI configs

▸ clusterctl credentials
    • synthesize ephemeral clusterctl config from provider env vars

▸ kind cluster
    • create kind cluster 'capi-test' (config: <ephemeral default>)

▸ clusterctl init on kind
    • providers: infrastructure=proxmox, ipam=in-cluster, addon=helm
    • infra provider image pinned/built if needed
    • CAPMOX image: v0.7.0 (build arm64 if needed)

▸ Workload Cluster — Proxmox
    • Cluster: default/capi-quickstart, k8s v1.32.0
    • control plane: 1 replica(s), VIP 10.0.0.1:6443
    • workers: 2 replica(s)
    • node IP range: 10.0.0.10-10.0.0.30, gateway: 10.0.0.1/24, DNS: 1.1.1.1,8.8.8.8
    • CP sizing: 1 sockets × 2 cores, 4096 MiB, scsi0 30 GB
    • Worker sizing: 1 sockets × 4 cores, 8192 MiB, scsi0 60 GB
    • Proxmox templates: control-plane=9000, worker=9000 (catch-all PROXMOX_TEMPLATE_ID=9000)
    • Proxmox pool: "capi-quickstart" (auto-created via admin API; tags VMs for ACLs/UI grouping)
    • Cilium HCP: kpr=true, ingress=false, hubble=true, LB-IPAM=true, GatewayAPI=false
    • Proxmox CSI on workload: chart proxmox-csi-plugin/0.10.0, namespace csi-proxmox, StorageClass proxmox-csi (default: true)

▸ Pivot to managed mgmt cluster — Proxmox
    ◦ skip: PIVOT_ENABLED=false (kind remains the management cluster)

▸ Argo CD on workload
    • Argo CD Operator + ArgoCD CR (version v2.13.2, operator v0.12.2)
    • CAAPH argocd-apps HelmChartProxy → root Application 'capi-quickstart'
    •   app-of-apps: https://github.com/example/app-of-apps @ main, path apps

▸ Final — kind teardown
    ◦ skip: PIVOT_ENABLED=false (kind stays — it IS the management cluster)

▸ Capacity budget
    • budget: 75% of available host CPU/memory/storage
    •   workload control-plane     1 × (2 cores, 4096 MiB, 30 GB) = 2 cores, 4096 MiB, 30 GB
    •   workload worker            2 × (4 cores, 8192 MiB, 60 GB) = 8 cores, 16384 MiB, 120 GB
    • TOTAL requested:  10 cores, 20480 MiB (20 GiB), 150 GB disk
    ◦ skip: host-capacity query: no Proxmox credentials available (set --admin-username/--admin-token or --proxmox-token/--proxmox-secret) (run with valid provider creds for live numbers)

▸ Workload allocations (per-bucket budget on workers)
    • total worker capacity:    8000 millicores, 16384 MiB (workers=2)
    • system-apps reserve:      2000 millicores, 4096 MiB
    •   ├─ argocd (operator + server + repo + redis), kyverno, cert-manager,
    •   ├─ CSI controller (provider-specific), keycloak (SSO), external-secrets, infisical
    •   └─ tune via SYSTEM_APPS_CPU_MILLICORES / SYSTEM_APPS_MEMORY_MIB
    • remaining after reserve:  6000 millicores, 12288 MiB
    •   ├─ database:           2000 millicores, 4096 MiB  (cnpg, postgres, redis, …)
    •   ├─ observability:      2000 millicores, 4096 MiB  (vmsingle, OTel, Grafana, Loki, …)
    •   └─ product apps:       2000 millicores, 4096 MiB  (Argo-deployed user workloads)
